Closes #2 

Adds initial repo structure with first endpoint and test, swagger, and marshmallow configuration.

pr_title: Add serializers for the Tasking Manager content
pr_body:
Closes #3 

As described in this [issue](https://github.com/hotosm/oeg-reporter/issues/3), add serializers for content that will be reported from the Tasking Manager according to the [Organised Editing Guidelines](https://wiki.osmfoundation.org/wiki/Organised_Editing_Guidelines)

Closes #5 

As described in [this issue](https://github.com/hotosm/oeg-reporter/issues/5) add git report to a git repository following all predefined information.

Tasks:
- [x] Implement report to any git repository
- [x] Endpoint for creating the report for a project
- [x] Endpoint for updating a reported project
- [x] Implement unit tests

pr_title: Add metrics and quality assurance to project
pr_body:
Closes #3132 

This Pull Request is part of the [issue of adding and updating fields according to Organised Editing Guidelines](https://github.com/hotosm/tasking-manager/issues/3132)

Add the metrics section to projects in the backend and frontend. 
This section contains two fields `quality_assurance` and `metrics`.

This Pull Request is with a WIP tag because we still need to validate if this field is going to be used with the Data Working Group, so we will wait for this validation to merge this.

This Pull Request is part of the GSoC' 20 project, for adding the Automatized support for Organised Editing Guidelines in Tasking Manager.
It will be updated in the next weeks with part of the new content.

Tasks of this Pull Request:
- [x] Report project data to a git repository
- [x] Report project data to a MediaWiki instance
- [x] Update reported project in a git repository
- [x] Update reported project in a MediaWiki instance
- [x] Add organisation option in frontend to allow Automatized Reporting
- [x] Add project backend field for indicating if the project was reported

- [x] Docker for a MediaWiki instance
- [x] Implement unit tests
